# QUICK START - Security Setup

## 1. Obtener Cloudflare Turnstile Keys

1. Ir a https://dash.cloudflare.com/
2. Turnstile → Add site
3. Dominio: `localhost` (local) o tu dominio
4. Copiar las claves

## 2. Crear .env Backend

`backend/.env`:
```env
# Local development
DATABASE_PROVIDER=sqlite
DATABASE_URL=file:./dev.db
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
PORT=4000
NODE_ENV=development
JWT_SECRET=airdrop-super-secret-key-change-me-in-production-12345678
JWT_EXPIRE=15m
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=0x4AAAAAAADe_tu_secret_key_aqui

# Optional Prisma migration connection helpers
# Use only if your deployment requires separate direct or shadow database URLs
# DATABASE_DIRECT_URL=postgresql://username:password@host:port/dbname
# DATABASE_SHADOW_URL=postgresql://username:password@host:port/shadow_dbname

# Production PostgreSQL example
# DATABASE_PROVIDER=postgresql
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@host:port/dbname

# First admin user setup
# ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@tudominio.com
# ADMIN_PASSWORD=TuPasswordMuySeguro123!
# ADMIN_NAME=Nombre del administrador

# Verification Services (Optional - mocks used if not provided)
# Twitter API v2
TWITTER_API_KEY=your_twitter_api_key
TWITTER_API_SECRET=your_twitter_api_secret
TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN=your_twitter_bearer_token

# Discord Bot
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_discord_bot_token
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your_discord_client_id
DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=your_discord_client_secret

# Telegram Bot
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token

# Wallet/Blockchain
WALLET_RPC_URL=https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/your_infura_key
WALLET_CHAIN_ID=1
```

## 3. Crear .env Frontend

`frontend/.env`:
```env
VITE_API_BASE=http://localhost:4000/api
VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=0x4AAAAAAA_tu_site_key_aqui
```

## 4. Install & Run

```bash
# Backend
cd backend
npm install
npm run dev
# Esperar: "Backend server running on http://localhost:4000"

# Frontend (otra terminal)
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
# Esperar: "VITE v5.x.x ready in XXX ms"
```

## 5. Test

```bash
# Login page
http://localhost:5173/login

# Deberías ver:
- Formulario email/password
- Widget gris de Turnstile abajo
- "Ingresar" button

# Completar captcha y hacer login
```

## 6. Backup Database

```bash
cd backend
npm run backup
# Genera: scripts/backups/backup-airdrop-20260423-134530.sql
```

## 7. Rate Limiting Test

```bash
# Intenta 7 veces rápido:
for i in {1..7}; do 
  curl http://localhost:4000/api/auth/login \
    -X POST \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"email":"test@test.com","password":"pass","captchaToken":"x"}'
  echo ""
done

# Verás:
# Respuesta 1-6: Error normal
# Respuesta 7: 429 Too Many Requests
```

## Environment Variables Explained

| Variable | Where | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Backend `.env` | PostgreSQL connection |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Backend `.env` | Signing JWT tokens |
| `JWT_EXPIRE` | Backend `.env` | Token expiration (15m recom.) |
| `TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY` | Backend `.env` | Server-side CAPTCHA verify |
| `VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY` | Frontend `.env` | Client-side CAPTCHA widget |
| `VITE_API_BASE` | Frontend `.env` | Backend API URL |

## Security Checklist

- [ ] Backend .env completo
- [ ] Frontend .env completo
- [ ] Turnstile keys válidas
- [ ] PostgreSQL corriendo
- [ ] `npm install` en ambas carpetas
- [ ] Backend compila sin errores
- [ ] Frontend compila sin errores
- [ ] Puedo ver widget CAPTCHA en login/register

## Common Errors

**"CAPTCHA inválido"**
→ Las keys de Turnstile son incorrectas o no coinciden el dominio

**"Demasiadas solicitudes"**
→ Esperado, rate limiting está funcionando. Esperar unos minutos.

**"Cannot find module 'helmet'"**
→ Ejecutar `npm install` en backend

**"VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY is not set"**
→ Crear/revisar `frontend/.env` o crear `.env.local`
